comments: The first one threw me for a loop and I had to re-read the short instruction at the top.  From there I was kind of nervous until the white carrot.  From there it was interesting the way that certain items felt more natural to call by certain more specific names.  I wouldn't call the sponge a "blue sponge" but I WOULD call the yellow jacket, a yellow jacket.
